President Obama has announced a Presidential Delegation to attend the Opening Ceremony of the 2012 Paralympic Games in London. The delegation will be led by U.S. Army General Martin E. Dempsey, the 18th Chairman of the Joint Chiefs of Staff. Other members of the delegation include Ambassador Louis B. Susman, Administrator Lisa P. Jackson, Kareem A. Dale (Special Assistant to the President for Disability Policy), Jean Driscoll (a U.S. Paralympic athlete), Sharon Hedrick (a U.S. Paralympic athlete), and Larry T. Hughes (a U.S. Paralympic athlete).